        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 11:15AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Light snow has begun in the lower-elvations of Beaverhead and
Madison Counties. This snow will continue through the next few
hours. The snow is reducing visibility to one mile or less.
Little to no snow accumulation is expected on roadways.

If traveling be prepared for changing conditions, make sure your
headlights are on, slow down, and use caution.
</description>
